{"books":{"35":{"id":"10710","title":"Shandygraff","description":"A number of most agreeable Inquirendoes upon Life & Letters, interspersed with Short Stories & Skits, the whole most Diverting to the Reader.  (Title page)    SHANDYGAFF: a very refreshing drink, being a mixture of bitter ale or beer and ginger-beer, commonly drunk by the lower classes in England, and by strolling tinkers, low church parsons, newspaper men, journalists, and prizefighters. Said to have been invented by Henry VIII as a solace for his matrimonial difficulties. It is believed that a continual bibbing of shandygaff saps the will, the nerves, the resolution, and the finer faculties, but there are those who will abide no other tipple.  (John Mistletoe: Dictionary of Deplorable Facts.)    Christopher Morley (1890 \u2013 1957) was an American journalist, novelist, essayist and poet.  Here are thirty-five of his humorous essays. - Summary by Book Preface and david wales","url_text_source":"http:\/\/www.gutenberg.org\/files\/13739\/13739-h\/13739-h.htm","language":"English","copyright_year":"1918","num_sections":"36","url_rss":"http:\/\/librivox.org\/rss\/10710","url_zip_file":"","url_project":"","url_librivox":"","url_other":null,"totaltime":"","totaltimesecs":0,"authors":[{"id":"2327","first_name":"Christopher","last_name":"Morley","dob":"1890","dod":"1957"}],"url_iarchive":"","sections":[{"id":"364546","section_number":"0","title":"Introductory:  Titles And Dedications; The Song Of Shandygaff","listen_url":"https:\/\/librivox.org\/uploads\/dlolso21\/shandygaff_00_morley_128kb.mp3","language":"English","playtime":"0","file_name":null,"readers":[{"reader_id":"6454","display_name":"David Wales"}]},{"id":"364547","section_number":"1","title":"A Question Of Plumage","listen_url":"https:\/\/librivox.org\/uploads\/dlolso21\/shandygaff_01_morley_128kb.mp3","language":"English","playtime":"0","file_name":null,"readers":[{"reader_id":"6454","display_name":"David Wales"}]},{"id":"364548","section_number